(9,	1,	'2025-04-24 15:56:36',	'2025-04-24 15:56:36',	'<!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"\"} -->\n<p>In <em>Hadestown</em>, the ancient world of Greek mythology finds a fresh, soulful voice through the rhythms of American folk and jazz. This Tony Award-winning musical, created by Anaïs Mitchell, reinterprets the tragic love story of Orpheus and Eurydice—two star-crossed lovers whose tale has echoed through the ages. But Mitchell’s version doesn’t stop there. The show is a mythological tapestry, weaving in the divine presence of gods like Hades and Persephone, and reframing age-old themes of love, trust, sacrifice, and the cost of doubt.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"\"} -->\n<p>At its heart, <em>Hadestown</em> is a retelling of Orpheus\' fateful descent into the Underworld to rescue Eurydice. Lured by the promise of warmth and safety in a cold, unforgiving world, Eurydice chooses the security of Hadestown—a grim industrial dystopia ruled by the god of the dead. Orpheus, gifted with music said to move even the stones, sets off on a harrowing journey to win her back. His song melts Hades’ heart, but the rescue comes with one condition: he must lead Eurydice out without looking back.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"\"} -->\n<p>The musical doesn’t shy away from the inevitability that shadows Greek tragedy. Even with modern melodies and poetic flair, <em>Hadestown</em> honors the core of the myth—it’s not just about love, but the fragility of belief and the high price of doubt. As in the ancient tales, the gods meddle and the mortals falter, trapped in a cycle as old as time. Persephone, the queen of the Underworld, brings seasonal rhythm to the narrative, her divided existence between realms echoing the ebb and flow of hope and despair.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph {\"className\":\"\"} -->\n<p>For mythology lovers, <em>Hadestown</em> is more than musical theater—it’s a revival of myth itself, alive with grit and grace. It captures the essence of classical storytelling while casting it in a modern mold, reminding us why these stories endure: because they speak to the most human parts of us, again and again.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',	'Love, Loss, and the Underworld: Hadestown Reimagines Ancient Myths for the Modern Stage',	'In Hadestown, the ancient world of Greek mythology finds a fresh, soulful voice through the rhythms of American folk and jazz. Learn about the myths driving this hit musical by Anaïs Mitchell.',	'publish',	'open',	'open',	'',	'news-hadestown',	'',	'',	'2025-04-24 15:56:36',	'2025-04-24 15:56:36',	'',	0,	'http://localhost:10034/?p=9',	0,	'post',	'',	0),
